HEADWORD: Intellected
<hw>In"tel*lect`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Endowed with
intellect; having intellectual powers or capacities.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In body, and in bristles, they became⟦br⟧
As swine, yet <qex>intellected</qex> as before.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intellection</ent>⟦br⟧
